(2) The following shall apply to citizens of Zambia— (a) shares may be offered at a discount to persons who purchase a small number of shares; (b) a share bonus shall be given at the end of a prescribed period to small shareholders who hold onto shares; (c) individuals, management and employees of the State owned enterprise may pay for shares in instalments; or (d) individuals may participate in the acquisition of shares which have been transferred in a State owned enterprise to a Privatisation Trust Fund which shall be established under this Act. [As amended by Act No. 9 of 1996 ]
